column.name: BODY
column.value: This conference breaks down all aspects of creating accessible web applications. We focus on the latest World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) standards in sessions discussing tables, labels, forms, images, color contrast, links, page structure, screen reader testing, and Voluntary Product Accessibility Templates (VPATs). The conference starts at 8am and ends at 4pm. Lunch will be served, with vegan options for those interested.

column.name: SECONDARY_BODY
column.value:
• 8am-9am: Tables
  • 9am-10am: Labels and Forms
  • 10am-11am: Images and Color Contrast
  • 11am-Noon: Links and Page Structure
  • Noon-1pm: Lunch
  • 1pm-2pm: Screen Reader Analyzation
  • 2pm-3pm: Voluntary Product Accessibility Templates (VPATs)
  • 3pm-4pm: Review and Q&A

column.name: BODY
column.value: This conference discusses all aspects of securing/hardening a web application. You'll learn how to protect against Cross Side Scripting vulnerabilities and SQL Injection attacks. Other topics discussed are virus protection, VPNs and port sniffing, phishing and malware, and handling data breaches. The conference starts at 8am and ends at 4pm. Lunch will be served, with vegan options for those interested.

column.name: SECONDARY_BODY
column.value:
• 8am-9am: Cross Side Scripting
  • 9am-10am: SQL Injection
  • 10am-11am: Virus Protection
  • 11am-Noon: VPNs and Port Sniffing
  • Noon-1pm: Lunch
  • 1pm-2pm: Phishing and Malware
  • 2pm-3pm: Handling Data Breaches
  • 3pm-4pm: Review and Q&A

Lunch will be at noon. It starts at 8 am and ends at 3 pm.

column.name: SUBTITLE
column.value: Ensuring Your App Meets HIPAA Compliancies

column.name: BODY
column.value: HIPPA compliance is required for any application that deals with sensitive data such as medical history of patients. In this workshop you will understand the requirements that must be met before release, with special focus on personal sensitive data. It starts at 9 am and ends at 3 pm with lunch served at noon.
